Both outputs are written and the transcript validates against the schema (21 iterations, 33 hypotheses, 32 analyses).

**Key finding:** feature_027 is the treatment. It produces ~+5 months PFS but only within the precisely-defined subgroup:

> **feature_006=0 AND feature_023=0 AND feature_022=0 AND feature_005 ≤ 5** (n=9,338; tx_eff = +5.01 mo, p<1e-300; outside the subgroup tx_eff = +0.02, NS).

The rule was derived by interaction screening, threshold sweep on feature_005, leave-one-out validation, and independently rediscovered by a virtual-twins decision tree. Dominant prognostic factors (independent of treatment) are feature_015 (+), feature_001 (−), and feature_014 (−); MV-OLS R² = 0.86.
